Members of the Bungoma Interfaith Network have said there is a need to reconcile Kenyans after the prolonged election period. The religious leaders met under the NCCK, Catholic, Evangelical Alliance of Kenya, the Muslim community, Hindu and other denominations. They said they are concerned with the increase in crime. They were at a press conference at Mabanga Farmers Training Centre in Kabuchai constituency on Thursday. They were led by chairman Bishop Callistus Baraza. “We the religious leaders of Bungoma under the umbrella of Bungoma Interfaith Network have for the past three days met in various forums and held consultations with our followers and county leaders on security,” he said. Baraza said the country has gone through a difficult period in the past year characterised by tension.  